> He was later elevated to the Supreme Court from where he retired in February 2013. he also served  as the caretaker chief minister of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa from March 20, 2013 - May 31, 2013.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://dawn.com/2013/03/21/tariq-takes-oath-as-interim-chief-minister-of-kp/ | title=Tariq takes oath as interim chief minister of KP | work=Dawn (newspaper) | date=21 March 2013 | accessdate=April 6, 2013}}</ref> On November 10, 2014, he was nominated as chief election commissioner of Pakistan.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-off}}\n{{Succession box |title=[[Chief Minister of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa|Chief Minister of Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa]]|\nyears=2013 &ndash; 2013|\nbefore=[[Ameer Haider Khan Hoti]]|\nafter=[[Parvez Khattak]]}}\n{{End}}\n\n{{Chief Minister of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Khan, Tariq Pervez}}\n[[Category:Pakistani judges]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Justices of the Supreme Court of Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Chief Ministers of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]]\n[[Category:Chief Justices of the Peshawar High Court]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{Pakistan-law-bio-stub}} MR. Tariq Pervez Khan passes away :18/4/2020\n", "name_user": "37.111.134.130", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(dates)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tariq_Pervez_Khan"}
